The paper deals with the problem of classification and reconstruction of high-dimensional signals from low-dimensional features, which is a common problem in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the application of the framework in imaging (cs.CV) and provides state-of-the-art results in compressive hyperspectral imaging. The use of side information is a common theme in multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI), which further supports these categories as likely choices.
